    <h2 id="executive-summary">1. Executive Summary</h2>
    <p>Jira Cloud and Th1ngs share the same fundamental concept — a <strong>Project → Issue</strong> (Box → Thing) hierarchy with typed issues, custom fields, workflows, and user access control — but they diverge significantly in richness of relations, sprint/agile constructs, permission granularity, and API shape.</p>
    <p>This document maps every Jira Cloud concept to its Th1ngs equivalent, identifies gaps where Th1ngs currently has no counterpart, and specifies the concrete technical changes (new entities, new REST endpoints, new YAML workflows, schema additions) that must be implemented <strong>before</strong> a migration can run successfully.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2 id="domain-model">2. Domain Model Mapping</h2>
    <h3>2.1 Top-Level Concepts</h3>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Jira Cloud Concept</th><th>Th1ngs Equivalent</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Cloud Instance</strong></td><td><code>Site</code></td><td>One Jira instance maps to one Site (SIT_ID).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Project</strong></td><td><code>Box</code></td><td>Project key → <code>BOX_KEY</code> (max 10 chars, trim if needed).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Issue</strong></td><td><code>Thing</code></td><td>One-to-one.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Issue Type</strong></td><td><code>ThingType</code></td><td>Map per project; share schema where types match.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Status</strong></td><td><code>State</code></td><td>STA_NAME + STA_CATEGORY (todo/in_progress/done).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Workflow</strong></td><td>Workflow YAML + DB row</td><td>Jira workflow → YAML file + DB entry (WFL_KEY).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Transition</strong></td><td><code>WorkflowTransition</code></td><td>TRA_NAME, linked to workflow.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Custom Field</strong></td><td><code>Field</code> + <code>FieldValue</code> subclass</td><td>Type mapping detailed in §6.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Version / Fix Version</strong></td><td><code>BoxRelease</code></td><td>BRL_NAME, BRL_RELEASE_DATE per box.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Sprint</strong></td><td><code>BoxMilestone</code></td><td>BMS_NAME, BMS_DATE per box.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Epic</strong></td><td><code>ThingType</code> "Epic" + parent relation</td><td>Needs a <code>TRE_TYPE</code> code for "parent-of".</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>User</strong></td><td><code>User</code></td><td>ACCOUNTID should store Jira accountId for traceability.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Comment</strong></td><td><code>ThingComment</code></td><td>COM_TEXT (CLOB), COM_CREATED_DATETIME, actor.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Attachment</strong></td><td><code>ThingAttachment</code></td><td>ATT_FILENAME with version suffix convention.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Link</strong></td><td><code>ThingRelation</code></td><td>TRE_TYPE integer must encode Jira link types.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Watcher</strong></td><td><em>gap — see §3</em></td><td>No native watcher entity in Th1ngs.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Sub-task</strong></td><td><code>ThingRelation</code> (type = "subtask")</td><td>Needs reserved TRE_TYPE constant.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Priority</strong></td><td><code>PrioritySchema</code></td><td>Entity exists; linking to Thing is a gap.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

