    <h2 id="gap-analysis">3. Feature Gap Analysis</h2>
    <h3>3.1 Gaps: Jira Has It, Th1ngs Does Not (Yet)</h3>

    <h4>GAP-01 — Issue Link Types (Rich Semantics)</h4>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th></th><th>Jira</th><th>Th1ngs</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Model</strong></td><td>Named link types (Blocks, Duplicates, Relates To, Clones, etc.) with inward/outward description</td><td><code>ThingRelation.TRE_TYPE</code> (opaque integer)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Impact</strong></td><td colspan="2">All link type semantics are lost unless TRE_TYPE is given a known mapping — <strong>High</strong></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> Define a <code>ThingRelationTypeDef</code> look-up table (or an enum + DB seed) mapping integer codes to names and inward/outward labels.</p>

    <h4>GAP-02 — Epic / Parent-Child Hierarchy</h4>
    <p>Jira supports a multi-level hierarchy (Epic → Story → Sub-task) enforced by issue type configuration. Th1ngs has flat <code>ThingType</code> with no native parent concept.</p>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> Add a reserved <code>ThingRelation</code> type code (e.g., <code>TRE_TYPE = 1</code> = "parent-of") and enforce one-parent constraint in <code>ThingService</code>. Alternatively, add a <code>THI_PARENT_ID</code> nullable FK column on <code>THING</code>.</p>

    <h4>GAP-03 — Sprints</h4>
    <p>Jira Sprints have: name, goal, start date, end date, state (active/closed/future), and a board association. Th1ngs has <code>BoxMilestone</code> (BMS_NAME, BMS_DATE) — single date only.</p>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> Extend <code>BOX_MILESTONE</code> with <code>BMS_START_DATE</code>, <code>BMS_END_DATE</code>, <code>BMS_GOAL</code>, <code>BMS_STATE</code>. Add <code>BMS_ID</code> FK on <code>THING</code>.</p>

    <h4>GAP-04 — Watchers</h4>
    <p>Jira tracks per-issue watchers for notification purposes.</p>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> New table <code>THING_WATCHER (TWA_ID, THI_ID FK, USR_ID FK, TWA_CREATED_DATETIME)</code> with unique constraint on <code>(THI_ID, USR_ID)</code>. New entity <code>ThingWatcher</code> and REST endpoints.</p>

    <h4>GAP-05 — Priority Field on Thing</h4>
    <p>Jira priority is a first-class field. Th1ngs has a <code>PrioritySchema</code> entity but no FK on <code>THING</code>.</p>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> Add <code>THI_PRIORITY</code> column (varchar, nullable) on <code>THING</code> entity.</p>

    <h4>GAP-06 — Resolution Field</h4>
    <p>Jira has an explicit <code>Resolution</code> field set when an issue is closed (e.g., Fixed, Won't Fix, Duplicate, Cannot Reproduce).</p>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> Add <code>THI_RESOLUTION</code> column (varchar, nullable) on <code>THING</code>. Set via workflow post-function when transitioning to a "done" category state.</p>

    <h4>GAP-07 — Time Tracking / Work Log</h4>
    <p>Jira logs <code>originalEstimate</code>, <code>remainingEstimate</code>, and individual Worklog entries. Th1ngs has a worklog box feature flag but no underlying entity.</p>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> New table <code>THING_WORKLOG</code> + entity + REST endpoints.</p>

    <h4>GAP-08 — Labels on Things</h4>
    <p><code>Label</code> entity exists in Th1ngs but there is no join table linking labels to individual Things.</p>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> New join table <code>THING_LABEL (THI_ID FK, LBL_ID FK)</code> + <code>@ManyToMany</code> on <code>Thing</code> entity.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2 id="technical-changes">4. Technical Changes Required</h2>

    <h3>4.1 Database / Entity Changes</h3>

    <h4>CH-01 — THING_WATCHER table</h4>
    <pre><code>CREATE TABLE THING_WATCHER (
    TWA_ID               BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    THI_ID               BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES THING(THI_ID) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    USR_ID               BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES USERS(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    TWA_CREATED_DATETIME TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    CONSTRAINT UQ_THING_WATCHER UNIQUE (THI_ID, USR_ID)
);</code></pre>

    <h4>CH-02 — THING table extensions</h4>
    <pre><code>ALTER TABLE THING ADD COLUMN THI_PARENT_ID               BIGINT REFERENCES THING(THI_ID);
ALTER TABLE THING ADD COLUMN THI_PRIORITY                 VARCHAR(50);
ALTER TABLE THING ADD COLUMN THI_RESOLUTION               VARCHAR(100);
ALTER TABLE THING ADD COLUMN THI_ORIGINAL_ESTIMATE_SECS   INT;
ALTER TABLE THING ADD COLUMN THI_REMAINING_ESTIMATE_SECS  INT;
ALTER TABLE THING ADD COLUMN THI_MILESTONE_ID             BIGINT REFERENCES BOX_MILESTONE(BMS_ID);</code></pre>

    <h4>CH-03 — BOX_MILESTONE table extensions</h4>
    <pre><code>ALTER TABLE BOX_MILESTONE ADD COLUMN BMS_START_DATE TIMESTAMP;
ALTER TABLE BOX_MILESTONE ADD COLUMN BMS_END_DATE   TIMESTAMP;
ALTER TABLE BOX_MILESTONE ADD COLUMN BMS_GOAL       TEXT;
ALTER TABLE BOX_MILESTONE ADD COLUMN BMS_STATE      VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'future';</code></pre>

    <h4>CH-04 — THING_WORKLOG table</h4>
    <pre><code>CREATE TABLE THING_WORKLOG (
    TWL_ID               BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    THI_ID               BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES THING(THI_ID) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    USR_ID               BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES USERS(id),
    TWL_TIME_SPENT_SECS  INT NOT NULL,
    TWL_STARTED          TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    TWL_COMMENT          TEXT,
    TWL_CREATED          TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);</code></pre>

    <h4>CH-05 — THING_LABEL join table</h4>
    <pre><code>CREATE TABLE THING_LABEL (
    THI_ID BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES THING(THI_ID) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    LBL_ID BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES LABEL(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    PRIMARY KEY (THI_ID, LBL_ID)
);</code></pre>

    <h4>CH-06 — THING_RELATION_TYPE seed data</h4>
    <pre><code>CREATE TABLE THING_RELATION_TYPE (
    TRT_CODE        INT PRIMARY KEY,
    TRT_KEY         VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    TRT_INWARD      VARCHAR(100),
    TRT_OUTWARD     VARCHAR(100)
);

INSERT INTO THING_RELATION_TYPE VALUES
    (1,  'parent-of',    'is child of',      'is parent of'),
    (2,  'subtask',      'is subtask of',    'has subtask'),
    (3,  'blocks',       'is blocked by',    'blocks'),
    (4,  'duplicates',   'is duplicated by', 'duplicates'),
    (5,  'relates-to',   'relates to',       'relates to'),
    (6,  'clones',       'is cloned by',     'clones'),
    (7,  'causes',       'is caused by',     'causes');</code></pre>

    <h3>4.2 REST API Changes</h3>

    <h4>CH-07 — Import Endpoint</h4>
    <pre><code>POST /rest/api/1/import/jira
  Body: JiraImportRequest {
    jiraBaseUrl: String,
    jiraToken:   String,
    jiraEmail:   String,
    projectKeys: List&lt;String&gt;,
    targetSiteId: Long,
    options: { importAttachments, importWorklogs, importComments, dryRun }
  }
  Returns: { jobId: String, status: String }

GET    /rest/api/1/import/jira/{jobId}
GET    /rest/api/1/import/jira/{jobId}/log
DELETE /rest/api/1/import/jira/{jobId}</code></pre>

    <h4>CH-08 — Watcher Endpoints</h4>
    <pre><code>POST   /rest/api/1/thing/{id}/watch
DELETE /rest/api/1/thing/{id}/watch
GET    /rest/api/1/thing/{id}/watchers</code></pre>

    <h4>CH-09 — Worklog Endpoints</h4>
    <pre><code>GET    /rest/api/1/thing/{id}/worklog
POST   /rest/api/1/thing/{id}/worklog
PUT    /rest/api/1/thing/{id}/worklog/{wid}
DELETE /rest/api/1/thing/{id}/worklog/{wid}</code></pre>

    <h3>4.3 Workflow Changes</h3>

    <h4>CH-11 — Jira-Compatible Workflow YAML</h4>
    <pre><code>workflow:
  key: "WF_JIRA_STANDARD"
  name: "Jira Standard"
  initial_status: "TO_DO"

  statuses:
    - key: "TO_DO"       name: "To Do"        category: "todo"
    - key: "IN_PROGRESS" name: "In Progress"  category: "in_progress"
    - key: "IN_REVIEW"   name: "In Review"    category: "in_progress"
    - key: "DONE"        name: "Done"         category: "done"

  transitions:
    - id: "start"   name: "Start"          from: ["TO_DO"]        to: "IN_PROGRESS"
    - id: "review"  name: "Send to Review" from: ["IN_PROGRESS"]  to: "IN_REVIEW"
    - id: "done"    name: "Done"           from: ["*"]            to: "DONE"
      post_functions:
        - type: SET_FIELD
          params: { field: "resolution", value: "Fixed" }
    - id: "reopen"  name: "Reopen"         from: ["DONE"]         to: "TO_DO"</code></pre>

    <hr>

    <h2 id="architecture">5. Import Service Architecture</h2>
    <pre><code>JiraImportController
    │
    ├─► validates request, creates Quartz job
    │
Quartz Job: JiraImportJob
    │
    ├─► JiraImportService
    │       │
    │       ├── JiraApiClient          (HTTP calls to Jira Cloud)
    │       ├── JiraProjectMapper      (Project → Box)
    │       ├── JiraIssueTypeMapper    (IssueType → ThingType)
    │       ├── JiraWorkflowMapper     (Workflow → YAML + DB rows)
    │       ├── JiraFieldMapper        (CustomField → Field + FieldValue)
    │       ├── JiraUserMapper         (Jira User → Th1ngs User)
    │       ├── JiraIssueMapper        (Issue → Thing + FieldValues)
    │       ├── JiraCommentMapper      (Comment → ThingComment)
    │       ├── JiraWorklogMapper      (Worklog → ThingWorklog)
    │       ├── JiraAttachmentMapper   (Attachment → GCS + ThingAttachment)
    │       ├── JiraLinkMapper         (IssueLink → ThingRelation)
    │       ├── JiraSprintMapper       (Sprint → BoxMilestone)
    │       └── JiraChangelogMapper    (Changelog → ThingChangeLog)
    │
    └─► ImportLog (persisted, queryable via GET /import/jira/{jobId}/log)</code></pre>

